        "timestamp": "2020-09-07 07:19:16.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nHi,\n\nI think, we should split the creation of the Tenant and the Availibility Zone.\n\nAnd here some remark for later.\nAt the moment the MULTICLOUD option is just handling the CloudRegion registration, which is fine.\n\nLater this should also set the MultiCloud option in SO call, as I have seen that is an option in the SO serviceInstances call.\nYou can set the \"Orchestrator\" within the call (see https://docs.onap.org/projects/onap-integration/en/latest/docs_vfwHPA.html#docs-vfw-hpa).\n                {\n                    \"name\":\"orchestrator\",\n                    \"value\":\"multicloud\"\n                }\n\nI have not tested it, whether it overrides the CatalogDB entry.\nI will add an issue in PythonSDK to support this.",
        "patchset_number": 3
